description:
Just a specific zoom of my east veil nebula which I like  :-)

------------------------
I had this project in mind for a long time : even the east part only of the Veil nebula are so vast , it really needs a wide field setup. With the new 24x26 CMOS, I thought it was a good time to have a try !

So I used my Newton 300mm F4 with the ZWO ASI6200.
Project of 2 frame mosaic

OIII nebula are finally more present than Ha, but you need a good filtering , the 3mm Chroma does a good job with that, the difference is impressive if you compare it with a larger band filter like a baader 8mm for example.

124 Halpha subs @300s gain 100 and -15°C
103 OIII subs @300s gain 100 and -15°C

20 Blue subs @60s gain 100 and -15°C
20 Green subs @60s gain 100 and -15°C
20 Red subs @60s gain 100 and -15°C

Total exposure more than 20 hours
title: Like a blue bird in the Veil nebula East part
